[Student "S"]
{This is a classic Notrump bidding sequence.

NORTH opens 1NT with 17 points and balanced distribution. 
SOUTH, with 9 points is not strong enough to bid game, but invites with 2NT. 
NORTH has a maximum, so she accepts the invitation.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:AQT6.54.A874.A82 2.QJ63.JT2.QT764 KJ84.AK72.65.K93 9753.T98.KQ93.J5"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1D pass 1H pass 1S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "33a79b8f3905999e35795413c4f0acd4dac5212fb7c4caa16313ebda94dcfb89"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{With two 4-card Majors WEST should respond "up-the-line", bidding \Hs first.

Then, after EAST bids 1\S, WEST has enough points to jump all the way to 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:KQT84.A7.KQ5.QT6 2.JT52.J873.9853 A963.Q64.A962.J7 J75.K983.T4.AK42"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1S pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "ecacdb9867d7c2db21a749d461fc1167e331766ed815a858c67d013518a47fa0"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 17 points and might open 1NT. But with the 5-card Major suit she prefers 
to open 1\S.

NORTH has excellent \S support but with 11 points is not quite strong enough to insist 
on reaching game. Instead he makes an invitational jump to 3\S, which SOUTH is strong 
enough to raise to game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:AK6.AJ9.AJ2.A852 T93.KQ752.53.Q64 87.T64.KQT96.T73 QJ542.83.874.KJ9"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b8281ae31788ea71679801f969e0bae99f3a1eb2a942064f9e35e583c65d4ae0"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_bidding"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has a powerful hand, but 21 points is not strong enough to start with a forcing 2\C bid. 
Since he has balanced distribution he opens 2NT (20-21 points).

EAST adds her 6 points to WEST's minimum and concludes they should be in game. She expects her 
good \D suit to be useful to EAST in Notrump so she bids 3NT.}

